channel.description: I have tried a thousand different codes, changed the compiler to my java and it didn't work. Can someone fix it on teamviewer or is there an alternative way?

item.title: 317 compiler
item.dc:creator: @matzie matzie
item.description:
@matzie wrote:

[quote=“Tom Hanks, post:4, topic:452694”][quote author=Dharma link=topic=555566.msg4067537#msg4067537 date=1344032884]

I have tried a thousand different codes, changed the compiler to my java and it didn’t work. Can someone fix it on teamviewer or is there an alternative way?

You need to post more information. What’s your compiler code and what error are you getting? Just asking for help isn’t going to get you anywhere.
[/quote]

The codes are basically all the same, that’s not the problem. The problem I think is that the jdk (“C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_18\bin\javac.exe”) isn’t mine but I tried replacing that line with my jdk version but it did not work.[/quote]

eye twitches i posted a universal compiler that works for everyone who has JDK installed. use the search bar and find it.
